[1] Canada (Alberta)
Date: Sat 24 May 2014
Source: 630 CHED, Edmonton [edited]
http://www.630ched.com/2014/05/24/2-more-cases-of-measles-in-edmonton-zone/


The Edmonton Health zone has 2 more confirmed cases of measles. Alberta Health Services says there is a case in Edmonton's north side as well as another confirmed for Sherwood Park.

There are multiple contamination sites in both communities [when cases visited and may have infected other people. - Mod.JW].

Kids in the Park Daycare - 2051 Sherwood Drive, Sherwood Park
- 15 May 2014 - 8:25 am to 7 pm
- 16 May 2014 - 8:20 am to 11:05 am
- 20 May 2014 - 8:35 am to 1:05 pm
- 23 May 2014 - 10:50 am to 5:45 pm

Royal Pizza - 590 Baseline Road, Sherwood Park
- 16 May 2014 - 6 pm to 9 pm

Ashmont Agriplex - Ashmont
- 18 May 2014 - 1 pm to 6 pm

Westgate Medicentre - 101, 9540 - 163 street NW, Edmonton
- 19 May 2014 - 8 am to 1 pm

Sherwood Park Medicentre - 101 Bremner Drive, Sherwood Park
- 20 May 2014 - 11:15 am to 3 pm

Dynalife Dx at Synergy Wellness Complex Lab - 501 Bethel Drive, Sherwood Park
- May 2014 - 1:05 pm to 3:15 pm

One case was a preschool aged child; the other was an adult. AHS says they're looking into whether the 2 were fully vaccinated.

This brings Alberta's total to 28 confirmed cases and 11 for the Edmonton zone. For more information on measles, including symptoms to watch out for and vaccine availability, visit the AHS website.

[Byline: Kirby Cohler]

