[3] USA (Oklahoma)
Date: Fri 30 May 2014
Source: Tulsa World [abbreviated, edited]
http://www.tulsaworld.com/homepage4/so-far-oklahoma-untouched-by-national-measles-outbreak/article_d3e815d1-6814-597a-b049-c66541ceee21.html


So far, Oklahoma has been untouched by the measles outbreak plaguing the nation. With 288 measles cases reported in 18 states since January 2014, the United States is experiencing the highest level of reported measles cases in 2 decades.

Measles cases have been reported this year [2014] in neighboring states Texas and Missouri, but no cases of the virus have been reported in Oklahoma since the late 1990s.

[Byline: Casey Smith]

