[4] USA (Pennsylvania)
Date: Mon 26 May 2014
Source: ABC 57 News [edited]
http://healthmap.org/admin/edit.php?id=2500003


Officials in Pittsburgh have diagnosed another case of measles and now are urging everyone to take extra precautions.

This is the 2nd case of the measles this past month and the 3rd case so far this year [2014]. Measles is highly contagious, and symptoms include a runny nose, watery eyes, a cough and a high fever. After 4 days, a rash starts, but infected people can spread measles even before the tell-tale signs of the rash kick in.

"People with measles are infectious 4 days before the rash starts and 4 days after, so those were places where that person had been during the time he/she would have been infectious," said Allegheny County Health Department Dr. Kristen Mertz.

Now doctors advise everyone that thinks they or a family member might have measles to call their doctor and the health department ahead of time before they show up at the doctor's office.

[Byline: Peter Johnson]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[ProMED Correspondent Susan Baekeland has indicated that a subsequent report in the Pittsburgh Post Gazette on Fri 30 May 2014 has stated that: "This measles case in Allegheny County turns out to be false
[see: http://www.post-gazette.com/news/health/2014/05/30/Measles-cas/stories/201405300206#ixzz33KNdM5od].

The possible case of the measles reported last weekend has turned out to be a false alarm, according to Allegheny County Health. The person, whom Health Department officials did not identify, tested negative for measles after testing was conducted by the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. The person had symptoms that were similar to measles, spokesman Guillermo Cole said."

Allegheny County, it seems, will not contribute to those higher numbers with this latest incident. But 2 earlier measles cases were reported in the county: in February and again in May 2014. Those cases were the 1st in the county since 2009. - Mod.CP

