[8] Kazakhstan (Shymkent)
Date: Sat 31 May 2014
Source: 24kz TV News Channel [in Russian, trans. abbreviated Mod.CP, edited]
http://24.kz/ru/news/regions/item/9390-kor-obnaruzhili-u-kursanta-v-yuzhnom-kazakhstane


Measles virus infection has been diagnosed in one of a group of 40 cadets arriving at the Shumkent Training Centre in Southern Kazakhstan from Astana, the capital city. As a consequence, the group has been quarantined and has been confined to the Infectious Diseases Hospital. According to the management of the training centre, the 40 cadets arrived on 12 May 2014, and one already showed symptoms of measles. The quarantine will be maintained until 12 Jun 2014, during which time the students will continue their truing course. During this period, all visits will be prohibited.

As immunity following vaccination is protective for life, it must be concluded that the infected cadet had never been vaccinated previously.

