[12] Micronesia
Date: Tue 27 May 2014
Source: ABC Radio Australia [edited]
http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/international/radio/program/pacific-beat/micronesian-measles-outbreak-puts-marshall-islands-on-high-alert/1317082


Health authorities in the Marshall Islands are on alert following an outbreak of measles on the nearby island of Kosrae, in the Federated States of Micronesia. Two cases were confirmed late last week, both infants, and the fear is that the highly contagious disease could spread to the Marshall Islands, which are linked to Kosrae by airline service.

According to Julia Alfred, the Secretary of Health in Marshall Islands, in the capital Majuro, medical officials are focusing on making sure children are immunised.

[Byline: Brian Abbott]

